CS_ASSAULT_HOSTEL by Patzilla / fenceareus (released November 2009)

It's not the another clone of cs_ assault, and it's rather an original author's variation of cs_mansion.

Here is a two-storeyed country house in the yard surrounded high fence. Terrorists spawn in the building, CTs - behind a fence.

Five hostages are placed in rooms on both floors of a country house.

Here it is possible to use ample opportunities for maneuvering, bypassing the yard and a country house from all directions. And open windows in the building aren't present. But there is couple of balconies, the pool in a small court yard and a labyrinth from a cut bushes.

More or less playable NAV-file for playing against the Bots embedded in BSP.

Thanks Patzilla for its nice map (and also for its other remarkable map cs_boathouse_hdr).

Play and Enjoy!

Description
==================
This is my second map I created for Counter-Strike: Source. It was actually created for the "Time Traveller" Mapping Contest in September 2011 but unfortunately I did not make it in time so I decided to take my time and put more effort in it. The map takes place in the same district as it does in cs_assault but about 50 years later. Much has changed in that time, the whole warehouse has been completely rebuilt, huge skyscrapers are gathered around the small old buildings and the railroad station has now two tracks! I have played much around with lighting effects to create a new, shiny and futuristic look.

Gameplay
==================
The gameplay should be the same as it is in the original version of cs_assault since the task was to only change the look but not the structure of the map. However, certain spots might differ a bit from the orginal.

Update
==================
- added small railroadtrack parts inside tunnel
- added playerclip brush near office
- changed texture at the station near office
- improved textures on warehouse gate
- added areaportals to the warehouse
- changed light sprite scale from 3 to 2.5 inside warehouse
- added viscluster
- added playerclip brush near counter-terrorist spawn
- added light inside the alley near counter-terrorist spawn
- added Hint/Skip brushes

Installation
==================
Extract the bsp-file from the zip folder into the directory

**c:\programs\Steam\steamapps\[username]\counter-strike\source\cstrike\maps**

(default Steam directory)

Feedback
==================
**Any feedback will be appreciated!** Tell me which visual changes I should do the next time I (maybe) recreate another map. What do you like especially about the futuristic look of the map? Does it fit well? What should I have done better in your opinion? I would love to know!

This map was designed upon request from James and the Hiven Clan, who are the valued sponsors of Dimension Studios. The map's dimensions and layout more closely resemble that of the original CS 1.6 version than TurtleRock's Source remake. Nevertheless the map includes all the advanced graphical feature that the current Source engine has to offer. This version of the map supports HDR and is recommeneded to be played with it enabled. The map has 32 spawn points to support a full classic CSS server and supports the latest CSS radar updates. Hand tuned navigation file is included for better bot and hostage performance. All the custom content except the nav file is bspzipped for ease in installation.

This is my first submission to Gamebanana! (Not my first map)

A bit of backstory:
In the century following a lethal strike into the Marr Freight Company which had been secretly been receiving illicit funds packaged inside certain products, the district's property values declined sharply. After a swift and silent coup d'etat a radical governor took power in the mountain city. Since then strict cleanliness laws have been imposed on the city. These are however, only enforced with those firms that pay a higher tax annually. Where does that money go? Nobody knows. What is known is that those businesses that fail to jump on this pricey bandwagon end up out of business and rundown.

Taking place in on the sketchy border between the good and bad sides of town, this scene sees the clashing of elite police forces and disgruntled small business owners  under the moon.

---

This is beta 2 of my map and close to finished.  

It's being played at www.tacticalgamer.com servers.

The CT's must access the computer building to unlock the doors to the armory near their spawn.  Once this is done they can access the underground very quickly.  

There is a door that can be locked and the latch can be shot and broken.

Please leave feedback for the next update and hopefully final.  I look at teamplay based feedback.

Correction (!):

The .res file (it is a list of files for server's client to to download all of materials need for current map) have mistake. This is the link to fixed file:

http://predator-koszalin2004.fm.interia.pl/files/cs_arcticstorm_pache_1.01.rar

It's recommandet specially for the servers.


Notice:

1. Hostages are like penguins. They can't use ladders.
2. If You want to have a fun, play with many players on this map. It's a little big one.


Briefing:

Terrorists have taken control over the sience laboratory somewhere in Arctic. They planning to escape with the new type of virus and sell them at the black market. They attacked when some of blocks of the complex are closed, and at the night when there isn't many guards. The silent alert has been activated and counter-terrorists are coming. Terrorists have taken four hostages to try a trade with CTs.


About the map:

This map is dedicated to CS:S servers with many slots (CT/T spawns: 32 - max players: 64). The map is a little big so I think 3 minutes per round isn't correct time to rescue the hostages with breaking through the enemy lines. 4 or even 3.5 minutes should be OK. Generally there are 3 ways to hostages, but only 2 You can use to transport hostages (they can't use a ladder). You have to get them on the helipad or to APCs (2 rescue zones).

This map has many options on attacking the other side, it will not get boring! 

   (1) Ware House
 
In the Warehouse where you see all the boxes, in the middle there is a solid box and on both sides there is a breakable box, so this is not your typical attack as you can shoot the box and see the enemy coming or hide and do a close range fire fight.

   (2) Street

Using smoke grenades and flash bang is a good way for a Terrorist to advance into the underpass and is a good middle point. If you run into the office or Ware House and notice no one is coming in that direction fall back and flank the CT's. I think it will be kind of tricky to snipe as a Terrorist because there are 3 areas people can come out of and the sniper can get flanked kinda easy if they are not paying attention around them.

   (3) Office

Good place for mid range snipe weapons smoke and flash bang will help a lot to advance to the break area to advance.
I hope you enjoy playing the map as much I enjoyed creating it. Please email me feedback so I can make a final revision.

Background :

Four highly valued weapon scientists have been threatened to be taken by a terrorist network. The scientists have been put into a "safe house", some apartments in the city, where they can hide until the threat is dispersed. Unfortunately, the terrorists found their hideout. In the attempt to capture the scientists, their getaway became compromised by counter-terrorists. Now, they have to take the scientists as hostages. The terrorists started to build barricades, but they weren't fast enough...

Counter-Terrorists :

Lead the hostages to one of the rescue zones or eliminate all terrorists, before the mission time goes out. The hostages are expected to be in the apartments west of the insert point. The rescue zones are located by the river and in the street north of the apartments.

Terrorists :

Prevent the counter-terrorists from rescuing the hostages or eliminate all counter-terrorists.

Ancient Arctic Ruins - Hostage Rescue 

Description:
------------
In a cold and snow filled valley are the ancient ruins of a lost civilization.  The strong winds 
howl around people who trespass on these hallowed grounds.  Some terrorists have 
captured some prominent scientists and are try to extort large sums of money for their safe return.

Objective:
------------
CT Team: Move swiftly to the other side of the map & enter the ancient mountain fortress to rescue the hostages from their jail cells. Then take them safely to the "Knight's Temple" or "Alter of Time".
Terrorists: Your objective is to keep the CT team out of your fortress.  Kill them all!
Note: This map has 6 medical boxes & the "Alter of Time" which will heal you. They respawn after 75 seconds.

Title			: Ancient Arctic Ruins
Author			: Redclaw
Release Date		: August 6, 2008
File name		: cs_ancient_arctic_ruins_v1.bsp 
IM/Email Address	: tachyonrays@hotmail.com
Website			: http://home.comcast.net/~redclaws/
Max Players		: (32) 16 vs. 16

Intro
------------
By way of introduction, I am "Redclaw" and I have spent the last 4 years mapping for AVP2. I also served as a map reviewer for PlanetAVP. 
About 6 months ago I jumped in the Half Life 2 and CounterStrike arena feet first. It's been a total blast and I love the HL2 world. 
If play AVP2 and would like to check out those maps please PM me.

Installation
------------

Unzip the files cs_ancient_arctic_ruins_v1.bsp:
Steam\Steamapps\<>\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\

WARNING
------------
Changing the map name from "cs_ancient_arctic_ruins_v1.bsp" to anything else will cause
all the special visual effects (specularity) to stop working as the cubemaps have been compiled 
for this map filename only. Basically the map will look like crap if you change it's name.
